InstallBadge.js
---------------------------

The InstallBadge.js can be used to easily insert the Adobe AIR Installer Badge onto any site.  

REQUIRED: To use the InstallBadge.js file, you will need to get the playerProductInstall.swf file (from the Flash Player Detection Kit), the AC_RunActiveContent.js file (from the Adobe AIR SDK), and the AIR Install Badge (also from the Adobe AIR SDK).

First, you need to define the global variables before you insert the InstallBadge.js file.  The first three items define what version of the Flash Player will be detected.  It needs to be at least 9.0.115 for the Install Badge to function properly.  After that, you will need to define the version of AIR that is required, the AIR Application Name, and the URL of the .air file.  All of the other items are optional, but all are shown below.

EXAMPLE - Defining the Global Variables

<script language="JavaScript" type="text/javascript">
<!--
// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Globals
// Major version of Flash required
var requiredMajorVersion = 9;
// Minor version of Flash required
var requiredMinorVersion = 0;
// Minor version of Flash required
var requiredRevision = 115;
// AIR Version Required
var airVersion = "1.0";
// AIR Application Name
var airApplicationName = "Sample Application";
// AIR Application URL
var airApplicationURL = "sampleApplication.air";
// AIR Application Image (optional)
var airApplicationImage = "sample.jpg";
// Width (optional)
var flashContentWidth = 217;
// Height (optional)
var flashContentHeight = 180;
// Directory of badge.swf file (optional)
var badgeDirectory = "/swf/";
// Directory of playerProductInstall.swf (optional)
var expressInstallDirectory = "/swf/"; 
// Hex Color of the Button (optional)
var buttonColor = "FF0000";
// Hex Color of the Text Below the Button (optional)
var messageColor = "FF0000";
// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
// -->
</script>

After you define your global variables, you place the following code block where you want the badge to appear on your site.  The two JavaScript files will need to be included in the following order.

EXAMPLE - Inserting the InstallBadge.js file

<script src="AC_RunActiveContent.js" language="javascript"></script>
<script src="InstallBadge.js" language="javascript"></script>

If you have questions or comments, contact David Tucker at david@davidtucker.net

